name: Putnam County Health
tweet: Putnam County tops the list of counties for the rate per 100,000 of COVID-19 with a rate of 490.2. This is almost 5 times the CDC high-incidence threshold of 100/100,000.   The PCHD has seen a high number of cases in the last few weeks. Please #DoYourPart to reduce the spread!  https://t.co/AgAfjn2HoX

name: Putnam County Health
tweet: Putnam County remains at Red Level 3 in the Ohio Public Health Advisory System. The rate of cases (251 per 100,000) is elevated, causing the county to remain at Red Level 3. We encourage all residents to follow preventive measures to help reduce cases in our county. #DoYourPart  https://t.co/asvdFSk2tt

name: Putnam County Health
tweet: Gov. DeWine announced today that Putnam Co has the highest rate of COVID-19 cases in the state at 233.3 per 100,000. There have been approx 100 cases in the county since Aug 16. A recent golf outing and some family events and general community spread were identified as sources.  https://t.co/YcMPl0Sd1Y
